            <fr:addr type="user">jms-00L4</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>jms-00L4.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Equivalence relation">Equivalence relation</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>A relation <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E\colon  A\mathbin {\nrightarrow } A]]></fr:tex> is called an <fr:em><fr:strong>equivalence relation</fr:strong></fr:em> when it is <fr:link href="jms-00JX.xml" title="Preorder" addr="jms-00JX" type="local">reflexive, transitive</fr:link>, and symmetric:</fr:p>
            <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
 \forall  x\in  A\mathpunct {.} x\mathrel {E}x
]]></fr:tex>
            <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
 \forall  x,y,z\in  A\mathpunct {.} x\mathrel {E} y \land  y \mathrel {E} z \implies  x \mathrel {E} z
]]></fr:tex>
            <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
 \forall  x,y\in  A\mathpunct {.} x \mathrel {E} y \implies  y\mathrel {E}x
]]></fr:tex>
            <fr:p>We will write <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathrm {EqRel}{\mathopen {}\left (A\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> for the set of all equivalence relations on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors>
